OBX|4|FT|24532-4^CT Abdomen and Pelvis^LN|4|FINDINGS: Evaluation limited without intravenous contrast.   LUNG BASES: Left lower lobe consolidation with moderate effusion.  LIVER: Normal.  GALLBLADDER/BILE DUCTS: Absent gallbladder. Distended gallbladder within normal limits postcholecystectomy.  SPLEEN: Drainage catheter seen within the splenic abscess which measures at least 9.1 x 7.6 cm (previously 9.6 x 10.6 cm).  PANCREAS: Normal.  ADRENALS: Stable nonspecific nodularity of the left adrenal gland. Right adrenal gland is hyperplastic.  KIDNEYS: Punctate right lower and upper pole nonobstructing renal cortical calcifications. No hydronephrosis. No suspicious renal mass.  GI TRACT: Sigmoid and descending colonic diverticulosis, with persistent wall thickening and peridiverticular fat inflammation and fluid compatible with acute diverticulitis.. Normal appendix.  MESENTERY/LYMPH NODES: No suspicious lymph nodes.  PERITONEUM: No significant free fluid. No free air.  AORTA/VESSELS: Normal abdominal aortic diameter (<3cm). Aortic atherosclerosis.  BLADDER: No significant abnormality.  PELVIC STRUCTURES: No significant abnormality.  SOFT TISSUES: No significant abnormality.  BONES: No suspicious lytic or blastic lesions. Degenerative changes of the spine.||||||F
OBX|5|TX|24532-4^CT Abdomen and Pelvis^LN|5|IMPRESSION: Percutaneous drainage catheter seen within the inferior aspect of the left splenic abscess which is slightly smaller on today's exam. Sigmoid diverticulitis, partially assessed without IV contrast. New left lower lobe consolidation and loculated left lung base effusion.||||||F
