OBX|4|FT|24627-2^CT Chest^LN|4|FINDINGS: HEART: Heart size normal.  VESSELS: Coronary and aortic calcification. PICC line catheter with tip in the region of the mid SVC.  LYMPH NODES: No suspicious lymph nodes.  OTHER MEDIASTINUM: No significant abnormality.  LUNGS/PLEURAL SPACE: There is a moderate to large partially loculated left pleural effusion containing pockets of gas. Left lower lobe lung consolidation/collapse as well as ground glass and reticular densities which may represent atelectasis or infiltrates. Ground glass and reticular densities involving lingula and right middle lobe likely representing atelectasis. There is a small right pleural effusion with associated compressive lung atelectasis. Technical factors or superimposed disease prevent exclusion of pulmonary nodules (#PULX).   UPPER ABDOMEN: Drainage catheter seen within left upper quadrant. There is apparent decrease in size of left splenic abscess. NG tube seen with tip within left upper quadrant likely within stomach which demonstrates mural thickening. Evaluation is limited without IV contrast.  SOFT TISSUES: Left chest wall soft tissue edema.  BONES: Stable. Endplate sclerotic changes lower thoracic spine cortical irregularity likely degenerative in nature.||||||F
OBX|5|TX|24627-2^CT Chest^LN|5|IMPRESSION: There is a moderate to large partially loculated left pleural effusion containing pockets of gas. Left lower lobe lung consolidation/collapse as well as ground glass and reticular densities which may represent atelectasis or infiltrates. Limited evaluation of left upper quadrant without IV contrast. Drainage catheter seen within left upper quadrant. There is apparent decrease in size of left splenic abscess. NG tube seen with tip within left upper quadrant likely within stomach which demonstrates mural thickening. Evaluation is limited without IV contrast.||||||F
